class="image-copyright--copyright">Daniel Seidman</span></div></div></div><div
class="recipe-page--body"><div
class="ad-gpt-main"><div
class="gpt-tag " id="gpt-ad-vertical-top"></div></div><div
class="recipe-page--body-content"><p>Have you never cooked breakfast for childrenor drunks? Been a Boy Scout? Been too exhausted to even conceive of preparing dinner? Have you never had an attractive person spend the night in your bed? There are few things an adult American must know how to cook, but pancakes are one of them. The good news is they're easyalmost as easy from scratch as from a box mix. You probably have all the ingredients in your pantry right now. Go check. Fifteen minutes later, you'll have yourself a stack of pancakes.</p></div></div><section
class="recipe-container">
<section
class="recipe-info"><div
class="recipe-info-item recipe-info-total-time">
<span
class="recipe-info-label">Total Time: </span>
<time
datetime="PT15M" itemprop="totalTime">0:15</time></div><div
class="recipe-info-item recipe-info-prep-time">
<span
class="recipe-info-label">Prep: </span>
<time
datetime="PT10M" itemprop="prepTime">0:10</time></div><div
class="recipe-info-item recipe-info-cook-time">
<span
class="recipe-info-label">Cook: </span>
<time
datetime="PT05M" itemprop="cookTime">0:05</time></div><div
class="recipe-info-item recipe-info-difficulty">
<span
class="recipe-info-label">Level: </span>
Easy</div><div
class="recipe-info-item recipe-info-yields" itemprop="recipeYield">
<span
class="recipe-info-label">Yield: </span>
4 Servings</div>
</section>
<section
class="recipe-content">
<section
class="recipe-ingredients"><h3 class="recipe-section-header">Ingredients</h3><div
class="recipe-ingredients-group"><ul
class="recipe-list recipe-ingredients-list"><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
2 c. all-purpose flour</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
2 1/2 tsp. baking powder</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
2 tbsp. sugar</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1/2 tsp. salt</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1  egg, lightly beaten</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1 1/2 c. milk</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
2 tbsp. butter</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
syrup (optional)</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
blueberries, apple, or banana (optional)</li></ul></div>
</section>
<section
class="recipe-directions"><h3 class="recipe-section-header">Directions</h3><ol
class="recipe-list recipe-directions-list" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Sift together first four ingredients (to prevent lumps).</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">In a separate bowl, mix egg and milk, then add it flour mix, stirring until just smooth. Then stir in butter. (If you want to mix it up, throw in blueberries, a tiny dice of apple, or bits of banana.)</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Grease a griddle or nonstick pan with cooking spray or a little vegetable oil. Heat pan on medium for about ten minutes.</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Pour batter to form pancakes of whatever size you like. Cook first side until bubbles form on top, about three minutes; then flip and cook other side until it, too, is brown, about two minutes.</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Serve immediately with butter and syrup or hold briefly in warm oven.</li></ol>
</section>
<section
class="recipe-extra-content">
</section>
</section>
